{
  "texts": [
    "In theory, large encoders that are similar to the decoders can compress information well from the original text into continuous vectors for the LLM.",
    "However, smaller, well-trained models such as BERT, which have fewer parameters (as least 10 times smaller than LLMs), are capable of encoding semantic information effectively (Devlin et al., 2019).",
    "This will substantially increase compression speed.",
    "Besides LoRA, other PEFT methods, such as QLoRA (Dettmers et al., 2023), DoRA (yang Liu et al., 2024), and MoRA (Jiang et al., 2024b) are worth trying for fine-tuning the compression encoder as well.",
    "Combination of hard and soft prompts."
  ]
}